3. Constants
  Defining constants using #define and const.
  Example code for immutable values.

Sample File: variables.c

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int age = 20;            // Integer variable
    float height = 5.9;      // Float variable
    char initial = 'B';      // Character variable

    printf("Age: %d\n", age);
    printf("Height: %.2f\n", height);
    printf("Initial: %c\n", initial);

    return 0;
}

Tips :
  Add comments to explain each part of your code.
  Keep examples simple and beginner-friendly.
  Use meaningful names for files and variables.
